 Nikto

1. Overview
Nikto is an open-source web server scanner that checks for dangerous files, outdated server versions, misconfigurations, and common vulnerabilities.

Used for:
- Bug Bounty web recon  
- Detecting exposed admin panels  
- Finding outdated server software  
- Quick vulnerability checks on websites  

---
2. Key Features
- 6000+ checks for dangerous files  
- Detect outdated web servers  
- SSL/TLS scanning  
- Check for common misconfigurations  
- Identify security headers  

---

3. Installation

Kali / Ubuntu
sudo apt install nikto
From GitHub
git clone https://github.com/sullo/nikto
cd nikto

Docker
docker run sullo/nikto -h example.com

---

4. Common Commands
nikto -h http://example.com
nikto -h https://example.com -p 443
nikto -h http://example.com -Tuning x

---

5. Important Parameters
Flag	Description
-h	Target host
-p	Port
-ssl	Force SSL
-Tuning	Scan type selection
-output	Save results to a file
-Plugins	Enable specific plugins
-useragent	Custom User-Agent
-timeout	Timeout per request

---

6. Advanced Usage
Tuned Scan
nikto -h example.com -Tuning 123b

Scanning categories:
1 → Interesting file checks
2 → Misconfiguration checks
3 → Information leak checks
b → SSL tests

Save to File
nikto -h example.com -output report.html

Proxy Support
nikto -h example.com -useproxy http://127.0.0.1:8080
